Using the laws of motion

Maximum height, s = ut + (1/2)at2

= 4u + ½ (10)(4)2

= 4u + ½(160)

= 4u + 80

Initial velocity, v2 = u2 + 2as

0 = u2 + (2 x 10)(4u +80)

0 = u2 + 80u + 1,600

Solving the quadratic equation

u(u + 40) + 40(u + 40) = 0

u = -40ms-1
